 80	---
 81	
 82	## Development Setup
 83	
 84	### Step 1: Start the Local Blockchain Network (Hardhat)
 85	Open a terminal and navigate to the backend folder:
 86	```bash
 87	cd backend
 88	npx hardhat node
 89	```
 90	**Keep this terminal open!** This runs your local blockchain network.
 91	
 92	### Step 2: Deploy Smart Contracts
 93	Open a **new terminal** and navigate to the backend folder:
 94	```bash
 95	cd backend
 96	npx hardhat run scripts/deployAll.js --network localhost
 97	```
 98	
 99	This will:
 100	- Compile all smart contracts
 101	- Deploy them to your local network
 102	- Set up initial configurations
 103	- Run automatic mockup simulations
 104	- Transfer admin rights to the DAO/Timelock system
 105	
 106	### Step 3: Start the Frontend
 107	Open a **third terminal** and navigate to the root folder:
 108	```bash
 109	npm run dev
 110	```
 111	
 112	The frontend will start at: **http://localhost:5173**
 113	
 114	---
