Path: Lending (BC) + frontend/loan-management/backend/README-ARTIFACTS.md
...
 21	
 22	### 2. Manual Copying
 23	
 24	You can manually copy artifacts using any of these methods:
 25	
 26	#### Using npm script:
 27	```bash
 28	npm run copy-artifacts
 29	```
 30	
 31	#### Using the shell script:
 32	```bash
 33	./copy-artifacts.sh
 34	```
 35	
 36	#### Using Node.js directly:
 37	```bash
 38	node scripts/copy-artifacts.js
 39	```
 40	
 41	## What Gets Copied
 42	
 43	The following contract artifacts are copied from `backend/artifacts/contracts/` to `frontend/src/`:
 44	
 45	- `LendingManager.json`
 46	- `LiquidityPool.json`
 47	- `StablecoinManager.json`
 48	
 49	## What Gets Updated in App.jsx
 50	
 51	The deployment script automatically updates these addresses in `frontend/src/App.jsx`:
...
 97	
 98	## Testing
 99	
 100	You can test the address update functionality:
 101	
 102	```bash
 103	node scripts/test-update-addresses.js
 104	```
 105	
 106	This will update App.jsx with test addresses to verify the functionality works.
 107	
 108	## Troubleshooting
 109	
 110	### Error: "File not found"
 111	- Make sure you've compiled the contracts first: `npx hardhat compile`
 112	- Check that the contract names in `copy-artifacts.js` match your actual contract names
 113	
 114	### Error: "Permission denied"
 115	- Make the shell script executable: `chmod +x copy-artifacts.sh`
 116	
 117	### Frontend can't find artifacts
 118	- Verify the files exist in `frontend/src/`
 119	- Check that the import paths in your frontend code are correct
 120	- Make sure you've copied the artifacts after any contract changes
 121	
 122	### Addresses not updated in App.jsx
 123	- Check that the regex patterns in `update-app-addresses.js` match your App.jsx format
 124	- Verify the network name is correctly detected
 125	- Run the test script to verify functionality: `node scripts/test-update-addresses.js`
 126	
 127	## Notes
 128	
 129	- The artifacts are copied as-is, preserving the full structure including ABI, bytecode, and metadata
 130	- The script will overwrite existing files in the frontend
 131	- If a contract artifact is missing, the script will report an error and exit
 132	- The script creates the frontend directory if it doesn't exist
 133	- Address updates are network-aware and will use the correct stablecoin addresses for each network
 134	- The CORAL token address remains unchanged as it's a fixed address ...
