 5	## Environment Setup
 6	
 7	### Create Environment File
 8	Before starting, create a `.env` file in the `backend` folder:
 9	
 10	1. Copy the example file:
 11	```bash
 12	cd backend
 13	cp .env.example .env
 14	```
 15	
 16	2. Edit the `.env` file and add your private key:
 17	```env
 18	# Required: Private key for contract deployment (without 0x prefix)
 19	PRIVATE_KEY=your_private_key_here_without_0x_prefix
 20	
 21	# Optional: RPC URLs for testnets (only needed for testnet deployment)
 22	FTM_RPC_URL=https://rpc.blaze.soniclabs.com
 23	SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=https://sepolia.infura.io/v3/YOUR_PROJECT_ID
 24	```
 25	
 26	** Important**:
 27	- Remove the `0x` prefix from your private key
 28	- For local development, you can use any test private key
 29	- **To export from MetaMask**: Go to Account Details Export Private Key
 30	- Never use real funds or mainnet private keys
 31	
 32	## Quick Start Guide
 33	
 34	### Prerequisites
 35	
 36	Before you begin, make sure you have these installed on your computer:
 37	
 38	1. **Node.js** (version 16 or higher)
 39	 - Download from: https://nodejs.org/
 40	 - Choose the LTS version
 41	
 42	2. **npm** or **yarn** (comes with Node.js)
 43	 - npm is included with Node.js
 44	 - For yarn: `npm install -g yarn`
 45	
 46	3. **MetaMask Browser Extension**
 47	 - Install from: https://metamask.io/
 48	 - Create a wallet if you don't have one
 49	
 50	4. **Git** (to clone the repository)
 51	 - Download from: https://git-scm.com/
 52	
 53	---
 54	
 55	## Installation
 56	
 57	### Step 1: Clone the Repository
 58	```bash
 59	git clone https://github.com/DescLending-Project/blockchain-prototyping-sose2025.git
 60	cd "blockchain-prototyping-sose2025/Lending (BC) + frontend/loan-management"
 61	```
 62	
 63	### Step 2: Install Dependencies
 64	```bash
 65	# Install root dependencies
 66	npm install
 67	
 68	# Install backend dependencies
 69	cd backend
 70	npm install
 71	
 72	# Install frontend dependencies
 73	cd ../frontend
 74	npm install
 75	
 76	# Go back to root directory
 77	cd ..
 78	```
 79	
 80	---
 81	
 82	## Development Setup
 83	
 84	### Step 1: Start the Local Blockchain Network (Hardhat)
 85	Open a terminal and navigate to the backend folder:
 86	```bash
 87	cd backend
 88	npx hardhat node
 89	```
 90	**Keep this terminal open!** This runs your local blockchain network.
 91	
 92	### Step 2: Deploy Smart Contracts
 93	Open a **new terminal** and navigate to the backend folder:
 94	```bash
 95	cd backend
 96	npx hardhat run scripts/deployAll.js --network localhost
 97	```
 98	
 99	This will:
 100	- Compile all smart contracts
 101	- Deploy them to your local network
 102	- Set up initial configurations
 103	- Run automatic mockup simulations
 104	- Transfer admin rights to the DAO/Timelock system
 105	
 106	### Step 3: Start the Frontend
 107	Open a **third terminal** and navigate to the root folder:
 108	```bash
 109	npm run dev
 110	```
 111	
 112	The frontend will start at: **http://localhost:5173**
 113	
 114	---
